Global investors  bought a  net 19.8
billion rupees ($365 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 6.1 percent to 961.2 billion rupees, according
to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6
trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 22.5 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
